      "author": "wanghuan9",
      "description": "## v0.1.3\n\n### Improvements\n\n- Enable \"Sync after save\" by default for new installations, reducing the initial setup steps.\n- Improve remote state refresh handling for block-level incremental sync, reducing sync failures or false mismatches when remote document state updates are delayed.\n- Improve remote block id mapping, making incremental sync more stable for complex Markdown content such as repeated paragraphs, repeated sections, tables, and nested lists.\n\n### Documentation\n\n- Add the minimum `lark-cli >= 1.0.53` requirement, noting that older versions may cause `Untitled` document titles or sync errors.\n- Complete the English README with feature descriptions, auto-sync behavior, incremental sync notes, and screenshots.\n- Simplify screenshots to focus on the Obsidian action menu and Feishu/Lark history preservation.\n",
      "downloadCount": 1,
